.<img width="412" height="275" class="wp-image-975903" style="width: 800px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Queen-Elizabeth-II.jpg" alt="" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Queen-Elizabeth-II.jpg?width=412&amp;auto_optimize=medium 412w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Queen-Elizabeth-II-300x200.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Queen-Elizabeth-II-58x39.jpg?width=58&amp;auto_optimize=medium 58w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Queen-Elizabeth-II-260x174.jpg?width=260&amp;auto_optimize=medium 260w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Queen-Elizabeth-II-195x130.jpg?width=195&amp;auto_optimize=medium 195w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Queen-Elizabeth-II-115x77.jpg?width=115&amp;auto_optimize=medium 115w" sizes="(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px" /> Former President Dr Goodluck Ebele Jonathan has congratulated Queen Elizabeth II of Britain on the occasion of her 70th anniversary on the throne. Jonathan in a message of goodwill to the British monarch described Queen Elizabeth II as a legendary leader who is well loved by the people of Britain and highly respected in all of the Commonwealth and the rest of the world. The former President commended the Queen for the undiminished grace, respect, dignity and trust she has bestowed on the throne, noting that her record seven decades reign has brought more respect and admiration to the British monarchy. Jonathan further urged “Queen Elizabeth II to continue to deploy her immense authority and goodwill to causes that promote peace, hope, mutual cooperation and partnerships across the world for the good of humanity. “Once again, I convey my warmest felicitations as you mark this rare platinum jubilee and wish you more fulfilling years on the throne.”